Question: Describe winter season in your hometown (do not disclose the name of your hometown).
Answer:
The winter in my home is quite warm. The temperature is usually over ice point. There is hardly any snow. The air is quite dry, which sometimes really harms peoples' skin. There is not so much sunshine in winter so people would rather stay in home instead of walking out to enjoy the weather. Usually people do not like winter in my hometown because we do not have heaters in home, which makes our hometown feels cold. In addition, it is not beautiful because there is not much ice.